<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Stuart Mitchell, "Resale price maintenance and the character of resistance in the conservative party: 1949-64," <i>Canadian Journal of History</i> 40, no. 2 (August 2005): 259-289.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Anonymous, <a href="http://www.economist.com/business/displaystory.cfm?story_id=333673" class="external text" title="http://www.economist.com/business/displaystory.cfm?story_id=333673" rel="nofollow">"Handcuffs on the high street,"</a> <i>The Economist</i> 355, no. 8170 (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2000-05-13"><a href="/wiki/May_13" title="May 13">13 May</a> <a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a></span>): 62.</li>
</ol>
